  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\nExpect a built-in hook which provides props reading capability. \r\n\r\nAssume this situation:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nimport React, { useProps, useMemo } from 'react'\r\n\r\nconst usePeopleListLogic = () => {\r\n    const { peopleList, searchText } = useProps\r\n\r\n   const list = useMemo(\r\n       () => peopleList.filter(item => item.name.includes(searchText)),\r\n       [peopleList, searchText]\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    return { list }\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst PeopleList = () => {\r\n    const { list } = usePeopleListLogic()\r\n\r\n   return <List>{list.map(item => <Item {...item} />)</List>}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expect to have a convenient way to separate logic and rendering and without passing props to `useLogic` hook.\r\nWe have no such ability to implements this third-party hook, only react can.\r\n",
